@node Doczego "Purpose of the program."

Program is a MUI replacement of@{b} RequestChoice @{ub}command.

@{b}A few words...@{ub}

I often have been using 'RequestChoice' command with Directory Opus and
other programs. But system requesters don't look nice. There are some
patches of course, like Arq or Mrq. They slow down the system however. So
I've started to write my own 'RequestChoice', compatible with old one but
a bit nicer.@{b} RequestChoiceMUI @{ub}is able to replace original
command, so You can rename it as 'RequestChoice'. Now all programs using
old RequestChoice will be more attractive.

@endnode

@node Opis "Detailed description."

@{" Show an example " SYSTEM "Run RequestChoiceMUI Bar WhatANiceRequester _Beautiful|_Maybe...|_Awful!" }

You should run the command from CLI. It has following parameters:

@{fg fill}TITLE/A@{fg text}
Requester title shown on window titlebar.

@{fg fill}BODY/A@{fg text}
Text shown in a requester. You can enter several lines separating them
with '*n'.

@{fg fill}PUBSCREEN/K@{fg text}
Optional parameter specyfying name of a public screen to open the requester
on.

@{fg fill}CENTER/S@{fg text}
This is optional too, makes a requester to appear centered on the screen.

If You want all the requesters to be centered, use environment variables.
Just execute commands below:

C:SetEnv Envarc:RequestChoiceMUI.val 1
C:SetEnv Env:RequestChoiceMUI.val 1

or click @{" here " system "C:SetEnv Envarc:RequestChoiceMUI.val 1"} and all
the above will be done automatically.

@{fg fill}Examples :@{fg text}

C:RequestChoiceMUI TITLE "Requester" BODY "Delete?" GADGETS "_Yes|_No"
C:RequestChoiceMUI "My Requester" "Are You sure You want to delete*nall marked files ??" "_Yes, of course|_No, please!!" CENTER

Command returns a number of clicked button (counted from left to right, but
the first button from right has a number 0).

@endnode

